title: Grateful Dead Live at Red Rocks Amphitheatre on 1982-07-27
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw-> Sugaree, On The Road Again, It Must Have Been The Roses, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Peggy-O-> Little Red Rooster, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> The Wheel-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Playin' In The Band, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
phil zone three night run this was the last time i saw jerry play on left side afther the summer run he moved over by brent  put phil on the left  and the phil zone started for me   i allways hung in the left side but the crazy sreming jerry    seemed to end up  in my ear  it took a few more years to relise phil was  the driving frouse 
 behind the band   on opening night it was raining they came out and did a mind blowing  cold rain and  snow  the place just crack open like a thunder   it was my first red rock shows i drove from so cal it made every mile worth it i chased the band untill  94  brent was gone  and playing stadiums erea  was the beging of the end phil was singing  allmost peaking with new songs  but the scene got ugly   but there was some old songs they blew the dust off un broken  chain   loved to hear phil sing
Uneven levels mar good show The note that "mix/level/PA/technical issues throughout" is really on point. I'm sure this is a step up from the previous sbd but the levels are really uneven.
